<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hi,</p>

<p>To use boolean values in databases that can not save boolean values you save tinyint(1) values with 0 (false) or 1 (true).</p>

<p>To save boolean values it must test and convert to 0 or 1.
it is easier to use the quoteInto method</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$db = Zend_Db::factory('pdo_mysql', $dbConf-&gt;asArray());

$condition = $db-&gt;quoteInto('mybool=?', true);
echo $condition; // mybool=1

$condition = $db-&gt;quoteInto('mybool=?', false);
echo $condition; // mybool=0
</code></pre>

